main event: A silver object was observed moving rapidly and erratically in the sky over Navarro, Minnesota on August 22, 1952.
interesting points: The object was observed for 5-6 seconds by a civilian witness.
The object was described as moving at a 'terrific rate of speed' and in a manner unlike any conventional aircraft.
The witness was unsure whether the object was a balloon, aircraft, or something else.
The sighting occurred during the day, with other aircraft also observed in the area.
The report notes that the sighting did not follow the standard reporting procedures outlined in AFR 200-5.
photographs: no, there were no photographs included
